

NOTE TO PACKAGERS:
 
The explanations in the README.md to how to do packaging and installing 
Videomass2, include all Debian distribuition based, Slackware and based, 
MacOsX and Microsoft Windows.

===================================================

NOTE TO TRASLATORS:

To start a new translation, create a new folder 
(for example de_DE for the German language) with the following structure:

    /local
        /de_DE
            /LC_MESSAGES
            
Take the file with the `.pot` extension, located in the source /local folder, 
and copy it into the LC_MESSAGES folder, renaming the extension to `.po`. 
Now you can open it with a translation editing program (for example `poedit`) 
and then save it by generating a`.mo` file

Update the /vdms_SYS/app_const.py file by adding the newly translated language 
to the dictionary, for example:

    supLang = {u "en": wx.LANGUAGE_ENGLISH,
               u "it": wx.LANGUAGE_ENGLISH,
               u "de": wx.LANGUAGE_GERMAN,
               }
               
===================================================

HOW TO GENERATE A FILE `.pot`

